In article <CByo9H.K0C@fulcrum.co.uk> Ian G Batten, igb@fulcrum.co.uk
writes:
>What are drug dealers supposed to be using Cryptography for?  I realise
>that America is prey to mass hysteria, and the ``War on Drugs'' makes
>the Red Scares of the thirties and fifties look lightweight, but what's
>the credible threat here?  I would have thought that cars and guns were
>rather higher up their list of tools than DES boxes.

Criminals would use crypto to mask cellular communications and protect
their "business" records.  Guns keep you alive, but crypto keeps you out
of jail by making it harder to gain information for search warrants,
indictments, and convictions.

